GetUserById.comment: GetUserById retrieves a user from Accounts. The user may be penalized or deleted

ModifyUserGroups.comment: ModifyUserGroups updates the groups for the specified user

EraseUser.comment: Erase all PII related to a user in a GDPR compliant manner

Erase.comment: To be implemented by our internal microservices

EraseUserSystemRequest.comment: Sent to each of our services when doing a GDPR erasure. Referenced directly by other codebases.

subsystems.comment:
return any recursive systems notified as part of this erasure call. for example if workbench
has erased the user from discourse, return discourse but not workbench.

delay_seconds.comment:
set this to a non zero value if there are some async processes (eg tasks or feeds) triggered by
will wait before issuing any more deletion requests to other systems to avoid multiple concurrent
writes to a user.

EraseUserSystemResponse.comment: Sent back by each of our services when doing a GDPR erasure. Referenced directly by other codebases.

DidAction.comment:
Determines if a user has previously completed an action

actions are tracked client side, dont use them for enabling capabilities!

CompleteAction.comment: Flag a user as having completed an action, future calls to DidAction will return true

UndoAction.comment: Unmark a user as having completed an action, future calls to DidAction will return false

Crop.comment: all 4 of these are relative to the top left

GetEntriesForDesigner.comment: Returns recent designs submitted by this user

crop_coordinates.comment:
crop_coordinates are the top left and bottom right corners of the crop rectangle
measured in pixels as [x1, y1, x2, y2]
This is the format used by thumbor in the same order

AuditData.comment: Data useful for auditing and fraud purposes. Should be sent with any user initiated action.

project_type.comment: Should be one of these types https://github.com/99designs/projects/blob/master/src/ProjectBundle/Resources/config/config.yml

files.comment: Should be one of these types https://github.com/99designs/projects/blob/master/src/ProjectBundle/Resources/config/config.yml

tags.comment: Use tool_tags, design_tags or admin_tags instead

crop_coordinates.comment:
crop_coordinates are the top left and bottom right corners of the crop rectangle
measured in pixels as [x1, y1, x2, y2]
This is the format used by thumbor in the same order

page_size.comment: `page_size` is the number of results returned, defaults to 30

designer_level.comment: `designer_level` is the designer quality level, an array that can contain "top", "mid", "entry", or any combination of these strings

last_activity.comment: `last_activity` filters designers based on their last login time, can either be "online_now" or "within_7_days"

design_limit.comment: `design_limit` specifies how many designs should be in response

keyword_query.comment: `keyword_query` is the text value for searching over design tags and tools

budget.comment: `budget` is approximate service prices in USD cents. Note that this only works when child categories are selected; it is not yet implemented for parent categories or when no category filter is selected

certifications.comment: `certifications` an array that can contain "jimdo", "print-basics", "squarespace", "squarespace-staging", "prezi", "square-online-store" or any combination of these strings

Contacts.comment:
`contacts` a string that specifies whether to include or exclude all contacts which includes: users with whom the current user has active work with, users with whom the current user has past work with, and users who the current user has favorited
must be used with valid `user_id` parameter

crop_coordinates.comment:
crop_coordinates are the top left and bottom right corners of the crop rectangle
measured in percent as [x1, y1, x2, y2]

s3_bucket.comment: Files will be copied out of this bucket and into an bucket managed internally by workbench
